NAME: Cod Liver Oil  High Strength
REVIEW: I recently tried the Seven Seas High Strength Cod Liver Oil Tablets, and overall, I found them to be a quality supplement with several notable benefits. Here's a breakdown of my experience: Pros: High Strength Formula: The supplement boasts a high concentration of cod liver oil, providing a substantial dose of Omega-3 fatty acids. This is particularly beneficial for heart health, joint function, and overall well-being. Gelatine-Free: One standout feature of these tablets is their gelatine-free composition, making them suitable for vegetarians and those with dietary restrictions. The absence of gelatine also means there's no unpleasant aftertaste or odour often associated with traditional fish oil supplements. Easy to Swallow: The tablets are relatively small and easy to swallow, making them convenient for individuals who may struggle with larger pills. This is a plus for those who want to incorporate a cod liver oil supplement into their daily routine without any discomfort. Omega-3 Benefits: The Omega-3 fatty acids derived from fish oil offer numerous health benefits, including supporting cardiovascular health, reducing inflammation, and promoting cognitive function. With regular use, users may experience improvements in joint flexibility and skin health. Trusted Brand: Seven Seas is a well-established brand known for its commitment to quality. Their long-standing presence in the market adds a layer of trustworthiness to the product. Cons: Price: One drawback is the cost, as these tablets can be more expensive compared to other cod liver oil supplements on the market. However, considering the high strength and gelatine-free formulation, some may find the extra expense justified. Not Suitable for Everyone: While gelatine-free, these tablets may not be suitable for individuals with fish allergies. It's essential to check the ingredients carefully before use. Potential Fish Burps: Although the gelatine-free formula minimizes the risk of unpleasant aftertaste, some users may still experience fishy burps. This varies from person to person and may depend on individual sensitivity. Overall, it's a reliable supplement from a reputable brand, but users should be aware of potential allergic reactions and individual variations in tolerance. I hope you found this review helpful.

The studies on the health effects of EPA used 1000mg (i.e. 1g) as a threshold level - that's the mild anti-inflammatory effects, and the impact on mood. I'm a bit annoyed as I've just bought another bottle - I'm gonna search amongst the 2000mg Omega-3 options to see if I can find ones that cross that 1000mg EPA level. As for the capsule shape, it's a little difficult to swallow, however, I've discovered the following helps me swallow them: Sit up straight, place a capsule in mouth, take a large sip of water, and lower your head (as if trying to touch your upper chest with your chin) and swallow. Then I wait for a few seconds before taking the second capsule. Doing all of this, the capsules go down smoothly. Omega 3 is essential for women going through that annoyingly insane time in their lives...when things start to stop working! And all that useless insane stuff starts happening to us! Price wise, they might seem expensive to some, but you greatly run the risk of rancid Omega 3, when you buy cheaper options. NAME: Omega 3 Fish Oil
REVIEW: These tablets are 1000mg each. Recommended dose is three, making up the insidious claim of 3000mg. If you're comparing these with other tablets go with the EPA and DHA in a recommended serving and if that serving is three tablets -- like it is here -- then per tablet is of course a third of that. These tablets show a great 3000mg on the front label, but that is for the recommend serving of three tablets. So these are 1000mg tablets. I'm surprised that this is allowed because it could be dangerous in some instances. Certainly if your doctor has recommend a certainly level of EPA/DHA and you're trying to find a cheap tablet this marketing scam isn't helpful. At present when I check various fish oil tablets and compare actually amounts in each tablet and the number of tablets in each bottle, this product isn't anywhere near the cheapest. Personally, I would avoid this product for the various reasons I've outlined here. However, they are okay product, so 2 stars.
